DRTVSeasonIE already extracts series/season_number for each episode entry,
but emits them as plain '_type: url' entries, which discard all extra fields
when the episode is resolved. 'url_transparent' merges them into the final
info dict, so %(series)s and %(season_number)s work in output templates.
The episode extractor itself can't provide them: the season/show object is
missing from the episode webpage's embedded JSON.

On top of that, surface the artwork and show descriptions that the API
responses already carry but the extractor drops:

- DRTVIE: emit every entry of item['images'] as a thumbnail (wallpaper
  preferred, so --write-thumbnail keeps yielding the landscape episode
  thumb) instead of only the wallpaper; the portrait poster URL then
  reaches the info.json, where drtv-dl fetches it for film folders.
- DRTVSeasonIE/DRTVSeriesIE: add the show's description and images to the
  playlist result, so playlist metafiles (--write-info-json /
  --write-thumbnail) provide tvshow.nfo material and poster/season-poster
  images (portrait poster preferred at playlist level). Season items keep
  the show under item['show']; series items are the show themselves, with
  item['show'] tried first either way.

--- a/yt_dlp/extractor/drtv.py
+++ b/yt_dlp/extractor/drtv.py
@@ -16,6 +16,31 @@
 SERIES_API = 'https://production-cdn.dr-massive.com/api/page?device=web_browser&item_detail_expand=all&lang=da&max_list_prefetch=3&path=%s'


+def _drtv_thumbnails(images, preferred='poster'):
+    if not isinstance(images, dict):
+        return None
+    return [{'id': k, 'url': v, 'preference': 1 if k == preferred else -1}
+            for k, v in images.items() if url_or_none(v)] or None
+
+
+def _drtv_show_description(data):
+    return traverse_obj(
+        data,
+        ('entries', 0, 'item', 'show', 'shortDescription'),
+        ('entries', 0, 'item', 'show', 'description'),
+        ('entries', 0, 'item', 'shortDescription'),
+        ('entries', 0, 'item', 'description'),
+        expected_type=str, get_all=False)
+
+
+def _drtv_show_thumbnails(data):
+    return _drtv_thumbnails(traverse_obj(
+        data,
+        ('entries', 0, 'item', 'show', 'images'),
+        ('entries', 0, 'item', 'images'),
+        get_all=False))
+
+
 class DRTVIE(InfoExtractor):
